EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO TAXATION -- LEVY AND ASSESSMENT OF LOCAL TAXES
***
1 This act would amend the property tax classification system for the city of Pawtucket. Class
2 1 property would be increased from five (5) dwelling units to six (6) dwelling units in which at
3 least one unit is owner-occupied. This act would also establish class 5 which would include all
4 residential real estate of not more than five (5) units if no units are owner-occupied. This act would
5 provide that class 5 property tax rates shall not be more than one hundred seventy-five percent
6 (175%) of class 1 property tax rates.
7 This act would take effect upon passage.
